<taxonomicName id="AB5D306250FFDE3AF9D65106D6F684F5" authority="Fauvel, 1927" authorityName="Fauvel" authorityYear="1927" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia barquii" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="barquii">Ophelia barquii Fauvel, 1927</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="24E2C1627489DA5D912D4E9D8891AC33" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph id="872F595DD939B3BF1AEBBF66F6B5CEA7" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87D74F66611FE40BB14BAFE81BEBACEC" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Reported from Greece by 
<bibRefCitation id="A5E874E5C374F014D915371ABE4ADC47" author="Papageorgiou, Nafsika" journalOrPublisher="Estuarine, Coastal and Shelf Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="643 - 653" title="Multicausal environmental severity: A flexible framework for microtidal sandy beaches and the role of polychaetes as an indicator taxon" volume="70" year="2006">Papageorgiou et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
. Type locality: Mediterranean (Agay, France). 
<taxonomicName id="5CC2096BEF3708ADA50D1A054016E8B1" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia barquii" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="barquii">Ophelia barquii</taxonomicName>
was initially described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="8010F5948D887C80E2A64BD9E97E5EA9" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia radiata" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="radiata">Ophelia radiata</taxonomicName>
(Delle Chiaje, 1828) by 
<bibRefCitation id="A5014A09880E698633BDC08AF29D4055" author="Fauvel, P." journalOrPublisher="Paul Lechevalier, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Faune de France. Polychetes sedentaires" year="1927">Fauvel (1927)</bibRefCitation>
, who distinguished the European species of 
<taxonomicName id="7C6FC0C7FD834FE8187DC80F92843E98" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Ophelia</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="1F8D9A41BE093F131EA6BDA9E267910C" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia neglecta" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="neglecta">Ophelia neglecta</taxonomicName>
Schneider, 1892, Savigny, 1822, 
<taxonomicName id="35FC31654888F7298E8EAB1D98B7774E" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia radiata" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="radiata">Ophelia radiata</taxonomicName>
(Delle Chiaje, 1828) and 
<taxonomicName id="1D3AECEF602E05AA6AA4783CEDBF2045" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia barquii" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="barquii">Ophelia barquii</taxonomicName>
) on the basis of the number of gill pairs. This was regarded as an unreliable character by subsequent authors (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="6644407A314D4FEA2CC99CA33651C63D" author="Bellan, Gerard" journalOrPublisher="PhD thesis. Universite d'Aix-Marseille, Marseille" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Contribution a l'etude systematique, bionomique et ecologique des Annelides Polychetes de la Mediterrannee" year="1964">Bellan 1964a</bibRefCitation>
) who considered 
<taxonomicName id="2EB8A8D79B7CD36DA5CAA1017FD3A98C" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia radiata" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="subSpecies" species="radiata" subSpecies="barquii">Ophelia radiata barquii</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="5F118BADD86ECD803D639157E9FBFDEF" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia radiata" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="radiata">Ophelia radiata</taxonomicName>
synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="A304B061B326B207A31DF6C373789953" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia bicornis" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bicornis">Ophelia bicornis</taxonomicName>
. However, molecular and morphological analyses by 
<bibRefCitation id="0B04388C894A3930112F7B05FB4D2FBD" author="Maltagliati, F." journalOrPublisher="Biological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="101 - 113" title="Morphological and genetic evidence supports the existence of two species in the genus Ophelia (Annelida, Polychaeta) from the Western Mediterranean" volume="83" year="2004">Maltagliati et al. (2004)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="D7F2312D1C9C73CF23949D3F9338C44D" author="Maltagliati, Ferruccio" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="835 - 841" title="Taxonomic distinction of Opheliabarquii and O. bicornis (Annelida: Polychaeta) in the Mediterranean as revealed by ISSR markers and the number of nephridiopores" volume="85" year="2005">Maltagliati et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
clearly differentiate 
<taxonomicName id="54AD4E68DA71DFE44509CAAB5AEF870B" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia barquii" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="barquii">Ophelia barquii</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="C28EA3674A5AEC2893E889F1D905043A" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia bicornis" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bicornis">Ophelia bicornis</taxonomicName>
, the constant morphological difference between the two species being the number of nephridiopore pairs (five in 
<taxonomicName id="2D9EF54751F30EB131E5467D5D0F3A5B" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia barquii" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="barquii">Ophelia barquii</taxonomicName>
, six in 
<taxonomicName id="1A801F34856522E4A65116E8C3E875F2" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia bicornis" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bicornis">Ophelia bicornis</taxonomicName>
). See also comments under 
<taxonomicName id="26F28809BD6EB2D130C4D436DF1C0212" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ophelia bicornis" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bicornis">Ophelia bicornis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
